The paper deals with designing parameterized algorithms for graph separation problems, which is a topic in theoretical computer science. The use of tree decompositions and connectivity properties also suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves analyzing the complexity of the algorithms, which falls under computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of graphs and cuts suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the properties of graphs and cuts, which falls under graph theory (cs.GT).
